The Outdoor Advertising Association of Nigeria has commended the Lagos State Governor, Mr Babajide Sanwo-Olu for ensuring that the state is aesthetically safe for all residents. Speaking while presenting a 100 units of branded safety vests to the Lagos State Parks & Gardens Regulatory Agency, the President, OAAN, Emmanuel Ajufo, said the decision of OAAN to present the gift was informed by the conviction of the Executive Council to support both the Agency and the government of Sanwo-Olu. The OAAN President was received by General Manager of LASPARK, Adetoun Popoola. Popoola also called on the private sector to support Sanwo-Olu’s desire to make Lagos State both aesthetically fulfilling and safe for all residents. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 